            <entry xml:id="entry_7fsær" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>ᵆfsær</orth></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>æfsæræ</orth></form>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>челюсть</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>jaw</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <re>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>ʒonyǧy fsærtæ</orth></form>
                    <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>полозья саней</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>sleigh runners</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>nyvond argævdync, bastīǧync æj, yswængtæ jæ kænync æmæ jæ aǵy
                            sfycync; jæ sær yn nyllopʼo kænync æmæ jyn je fsær raxīcæn
                            kænync</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>жертвенное животное закалывают, свежуют, (режут) на части и варят в
                                котле; голову его очищают от шерсти и отделяют челюсть</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the sacrificial animal is slaughtered, skinned, cut into pieces and
                                boiled in a cauldron; his head is cleaned of hair and the jaw is
                                separated</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."
                            /><biblScope>206</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Метатеза из %i*sfær%i ← %i*spar-%i. Иранское слово; в живых
                    иранских языках закрепилось преимущественно за некоторыми предметами
                    материальной культуры: сохой, сошником, заступом и пр. Здесь, как и во многих
                    других случаях, имеет место перенос анатомического термина на орудия; см.,
                    например, под словом <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ar"/> ‘рука’, ‘оглобля’. Ср.
                        <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>spār, supār</w>
                        <gloss><q>соха</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>плуг</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/>
                        <w>äspärä, aspereh, isperek</w>
                        <gloss><q>заступ</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>изогнутая палка внизу у заступа, на которую надавливают
                            ногой</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="hac"><lang/>
                        <w>äspār</w>
                        <gloss><q>заступ</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>spāra</w>
                        <gloss><q>сошник</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><lang/>
                        <w>səpār, s(e)pōr, spōr, sepōrn</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"><lang/>
                        <w>sporo</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/>
                        <w>s'pēra, sparo, spara</w>
                        <gloss><q>соха</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"><lang/>
                        <w>spər</w>
                        <gloss><q>сошник</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="isk"><lang/>
                        <w>uspir</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yah"><lang/>
                        <w>s%rə%rpīr</w>
                        <gloss><q>соха</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/>
                        <w>s%rə%rpundr, s'por</w>
                        <gloss><q>сошник</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="srh"><lang/>
                        <w>spur, supur</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="oru"><lang/>
                        <w>ʽspar</w>
                        <gloss><q>плуг</q></gloss></mentioned>. Перечисленные термины, частью,
                    возможно, заимствованные из персидского, частью оригинальные, восходят к
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*spara-, *sparana-</w>
                        <gloss><q>челюсть</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>изогнутое орудие для рыхления почвы</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w/><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">а
                            также</note>
                        <gloss><q>соха</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>сошник</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>заступ</q></gloss></mentioned>. Значение ‘челюсть’ для
                    древнеиранского устанавливается на основании <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>sparnha-</w>
                        <gloss><q>десны</q></gloss></mentioned> из <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>*sparam-ga</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">буквально</note>
                        <gloss><q>что находится (%iga%i) на челюсти
                        (%isparam%i)</q></gloss></mentioned>, как <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>śṙñga</w>
                        <gloss><q>рог</q></gloss></mentioned> из <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>śiram-ga</w>
                        <gloss><q>нарост на голове (%iśiram%i)</q></gloss></mentioned>. В дальнейшем
                    возможна связь с глагольной основой %ispar-%i ‘попирать’, ‘крушить’ и пр. (см.
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_7fsæryn"/>). Менее вероятной кажется нам связь
                    с <mentioned xml:lang="srh"><lang/>
                        <w>pšūr</w>
                        <gloss><q>щека</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="srh"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>лицо</q></gloss></mentioned>. Ос. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_xsærfars"/> ‘щека’ представляет очевидную диссимиляцию из
                        %ifsær%i-<ref type="xr" target="#entry_fars"/> буквально „сторона
                            челюсти“.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Miller,_IF_21"
                            /><biblScope xml:lang="ru">стр. 325 сл</biblScope><biblScope
                            xml:lang="en">p. 325 ff</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">A metathesis from %i*sfær%i ← %i*spar-%i. An Iranian word; in
                    (not dead) Iranian languages, it was mainly assigned to some objects of material
                    culture: plough, ploughshare bone, spade, etc. Here, as in many other cases,
                    there is a transfer of the anatomical term to tools; see, e.g., under the word
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ar"/> ‘hand’, ‘shaft’. Cf. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>spār, supār</w>
                        <gloss><q>wooden plough</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>plough</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/>
                        <w>äspärä, aspereh, isperek</w>
                        <gloss><q>spade</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>curved stick at the bottom of the spade that is pressed down on by
                                the foot</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="hac"><lang/>
                        <w>äspār</w>
                        <gloss><q>spade</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>spāra</w>
                        <gloss><q>ploughshare</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><lang/>
                        <w>səpār, s(e)pōr, spōr, sepōrn</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"><lang/>
                        <w>sporo</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/>
                        <w>s'pēra, sparo, spara</w>
                        <gloss><q>wooden plough</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"><lang/>
                        <w>spər</w>
                        <gloss><q>ploughshare</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="isk"><lang/>
                        <w>uspir</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yah"><lang/>
                        <w>s%rə%rpīr</w>
                        <gloss><q>wooden plough</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/>
                        <w>s%rə%rpundr, s'por</w>
                        <gloss><q>ploughshare</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="srh"><lang/>
                        <w>spur, supur</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="oru"><lang/>
                        <w>ʽspar</w>
                        <gloss><q>plough</q></gloss></mentioned>. The listed terms, partly possibly
                    borrowed from Persian, partly original, go back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*spara-, *sparana-</w>
                        <gloss><q>jaw</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>curved soil loosening tool</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ira"><w/><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">а также</note><note
                            type="comment" xml:lang="en">and also</note>
                        <gloss><q>wooden plough</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>ploughshare</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>spade</q></gloss></mentioned>. The meaning ‘jaw’ is established
                    for Old Iranian based on <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>sparnha-</w>
                        <gloss><q>gums</q></gloss></mentioned> from <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>*sparam-ga</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">буквально</note><note
                            type="comment" xml:lang="en">literally</note>
                        <gloss><q>thing that is (%iga%i) on a jaw
                        (%isparam%i)</q></gloss></mentioned>, as <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>śṙñga</w>
                        <gloss><q>horn</q></gloss></mentioned> from <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>śiram-ga</w>
                        <gloss><q>growth on the head (%iśiram%i)</q></gloss></mentioned>. Later, a
                    connection with the verb stem %ispar-%i ‘trample’, ‘destroy’ etc. is possible
                    (see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_7fsæryn"/>). The connection to <mentioned
                        xml:lang="srh"><lang/>
                        <w>pšūr</w>
                        <gloss><q>cheek</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="srh"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>face</q></gloss></mentioned> seems less probable. Ossetic <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_xsærfars"/> ‘cheek’ is an obvious dissimilation
                    from %ifsær%i-<ref type="xr" target="#entry_fars"/> literaly ‘jaw
                            side’.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Miller,_IF_21"/><biblScope
                            xml:lang="ru">стр. 325 сл</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">p. 325
                            ff</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
